title: For Sale:  **12 Gauge pump Mossberg500AB 30" barrel  Red-Dot Scope //walnut
postcontent:
Mossberg 500AB 12 gauge 6+1 pump, beautiful gun, walnut, nice shotgun..with a picatinny rail mounted Red Dot scope. The 500AB is the 500A Mossberg shotgun with some improvements...specifically a Walnut stock VS the various hardwood stocks found on the regular 500A model. My 500AB also has some etchings in the receiver metal ,as seen in 1 photo, that the 500A does not have ...and it has a 30" barrel. (Every part on this 500AB is interchangeable with the regular 500A)
This is a fixed full choke 30" barreled shotgun. Thirty inches is a long range shotgun. Perfect for Deer /Water Fowl...and well, anything. You get the 100 yard reach of a rifle, with the spread pattern of a shotgun. Full choke means it keeps it's shot pattern tight over a long distance, so you get killing/stopping power at rifle like distances. It shoots bird and buck shot and rifled slugs. It is chambered for 2&3/4" and 3.00" shells. I'll include a box of shells with it...I won't need them if I sell the shotgun. It functions flawlessly and it looks great. The walnut is beautiful. The bore is beautiful inside...slick as a whistle. It also has a metal safety switch, not a plastic one like the newer Mossbergs. It has a Tasco Red Dot scope, a good one, that enables quick sholdering and accurate firing of shotgun. For those folks who don't know what a Red Dot scope is: You turn the switch on and the red dot is displayed in the scope lens.....when you look thru the scope, wherever the dot is - that's where the bullet goes. If you move your head, the red-dot stays on the target your pointing at and you can still see the dot as you move your head around. It makes for very quick and accurate shooting. I love this shotgun, and the new owner will too. I need money, I have to sell it. Three hundred is as low as I'll go. A box of shells #8, go with it. Thanks.

This is a rifle like no other. Patriot Ordinance makes some of the best battle rifles on the planet. I bought this for a hog hunt, but the rifle didn't arrive until after the hunt. I don't really want to get rid of it, but have other projects in mind. 

The list of features on this rifle are below, but don't really do it justice. 


Barrel
• 14.5" heavy contour hand-lapped button twisted rifled, fluted to reduce weight and heat.
• 4150 Mil-B-11595 chrome-moly-vanadium alloy (machine gun rated).
• 70 Rockwell case hardened (Nitride) heat-treated "5R" polygonal barrels are 2x harder than MIL-SPEC and hammer-forged barrels.
• Corrosion resistant, 10x thicker, and 10x harder than MIL-SPEC chrome lining.
• POF-USA  1.5" muzzle device.
• 7.62x51 mm NATO (.308 Winchester) chamber.

Method of Operation
• Gas Piston operated, rotating bolt (short stroke system).
• 3-position gas system for normal, suppressed, and bolt-action operating modes.
• C.R.O.S.™ (Corrosion Resistant Operating System) Nitride heat treated barrel, single-piece gas block, Nitride heat-treated gas plug, chromed gas piston, and NP3™ coated bolt carrier assembly (one-piece) all billet machined.

Bolt & Carrier
• Nickel plated 8620, integral keyed, steel bolt carrier (billet machined), heat treated/plated per MIL-SPEC.
• Roller cam pin, NP3™ coated.
• Chrome plated bolt, heat-treated to MIL-SPEC.

Upper Receiver
• POF-USA Modular Railed Receiver™ (M.R.R.™), free-floating handguard, monolithic top rail system, billet machined 7075-T6 aircraft aluminum alloy.
• 2-piece A3 flattop upper receiver.
• Oversized heat-sink barrel nut.
• Black Anodized charging handle.
Lower Receiver
• P308, GEN III billet machined 7075-T6 aircraft aluminum alloy with integrated oversized trigger guard.
• Ambidextrous bolt release lever machined into the lower receiver.
• Drop-in, single-stage, 4.5 lb. non-adjustable trigger system.
• Magpul™ MOE™ pistol grip.
• KNS™ Precision anti-walk pins.
• Ambidextrous selector switch.
• NORGON ambidextrous magazine release.
• Magpul™ STR™ 7-position retractable buttstock.
• Anti-tilt buffer tube with four drain holes for marine use.
• Black Anodized, NP3™, or Olive Drab Cerakote™ finishes.

Handguard
• POF-USA free-floating Modular Railed Receiver™ (M.R.R.™).
• Detachable handguard rail estate for large objective lens scopes.
• ERGO™ ladder rail covers.
• Single-piece sling/bi-pod mount.

Magazine
• 1 - 20-round Magpul™ PMAG™ polymer magazine included.

Weights
• 8.5 lbs. (empty)

Manufacturing
• All raw materials, heat-treats, platings/coatings, accessories, and component parts on our weapon systems are made 100% through U.S. owned and operated steel mills and manufacturers.
